# Framework Pass 1 - Design & Implement Manifest

<audit_manifest>
  <audit_type>framework_pass1</audit_type>

  <purpose>
    Design and implement token-efficient governance and manifest framework using root-level governance files, nested per-folder CLAUDE.md, and nested manifest files.
  </purpose>

  <scope>
    - Discover project structure (top 2-3 levels)
    - Create root governance files (CLAUDE.md, GOVERNANCE.md, CONTEXT_BOUNDARY.md, MODEL_GUIDANCE.md, TASK_PATTERNS.md, TAGS.md, DOMAIN_KNOWLEDGE.md)
    - Set up nested manifests and per-folder CLAUDE files
  </scope>

  <constraints>
    - Token efficiency in reasoning and output
    - Short bullet lists, diffs only
    - No restatement of prompt
    - Keep CLAUDE.md <= 150-200 lines
    - Folder manifest.md <= 30-40 lines
  </constraints>

  <required_inputs>
    - Repository tree (top 2-3 levels)
    - Existing governance files (if any)
    - Main domain folders identification
  </required_inputs>

  <expected_outputs>
    - Root governance files created/updated
    - Per-folder manifest.md files
    - Per-folder CLAUDE.md files (where appropriate)
    - Short summary of files created/updated
  </expected_outputs>

  <activation_conditions>
    - Initial project setup
    - Major restructuring of governance framework
  </activation_conditions>

  <run_pattern>
    1. Inspect repo tree, identify domains
    2. Create root governance files with tagged sections
    3. Create folder-level manifests and CLAUDE.md
    4. Output short summary only
  </run_pattern>
</audit_manifest>
